text: Sitala palmaria is a species of air-breathing land snail, terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicarionidae. == Distribution == This species occurs in India, and was described from Nandi Hills, India by malacologist William Henry Benson in 1864. == References == Category:Helicarionidae Category:Gastropods described in 1864 Category:Taxa named by William Henry Benson
title: Sitala palmaria
